Gunmen on Sunday attacked another police station in Anambra State. One policeman was allegedly injured. But, efforts by the gunmen to burn down the police post located at Mgbakwu in Awka North Local Government were repelled by the policemen on duty. The Nation gathered that the hoodlums shot sporadically to scare everyone, to give them the opportunity to set the police post ablaze. But they met resistance from the policemen on duty. One of the policemen was injured by the hoodlums, who ran away when they faced superior gun power from the police. A source said the injured policeman had been taken to hospital. Confirming the incident, spokesman Ikenga Tochukwu said the efforts of their men prevented the hoodlums from setting ablaze the police station. He, however, he did not say whether any policeman was injured or killed.